---
title: Silky Sicilian Penne tossed with Zucchini, Mushrooms & Tomatoes
description: If you’re mad for mushrooms, a fan of fungi, or crazy for creminis, this pasta will treat you right: It’s loaded with ’shroom slices! They’re the flavor backbone of this recipe along with rich mushroom stock, bringing all those deep, earthy flavors that you know and love. We’ve added al dente penne, a lemony, chive-flecked crème fraîche sauce, zucchini and tomatoes, and a sprinkling of Parmesan cheese. Get ready for this umami-packed dish to hit your dinner table.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/60a517b5b4a01c17f624c081-6b5f2177.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/silky-sicilian-penne-60a517b5b4a01c17f624c081-7cbb3be8.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 690 kcal
  fat: 34 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 85 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 20 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 530 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/silky-sicilian-penne-60a517b5b4a01c17f624c081
course: main course
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim and quarter @zucchini{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthwise); cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @cremini mushrooms{4%ounce}. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Mince @chives{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Transfer to a medium #bowl{}.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Turn off heat; season with salt and pepper, then transfer to bowl with zucchini. Wash out pan.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain well.

While penne cooks, heat @butter{1%tablespoon} and a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for mushrooms over medium-high heat. Add tomatoes and season with @Italian seasoning{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper. (Use the rest of the Italian seasoning as you like.) Cook, stirring, until tomatoes are softened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Stir in half the chives and juice from half the lemon. Reduce heat to low, then stir in @mushroom stock concentrate{1} and ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water.

Whisk in @crème fraîche{4%tablespoon}; season with salt and pepper.

Add zucchini, mushrooms, and drained penne to pan with sauce; stir to combine. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted.

> TIP: If necessary, add more pasta cooking water a splash at a time until penne is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and remaining chives. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.